In addition to prediction accuracy, we compared the technical and advanced features of each algorithms. The technical features include the prediction approach, the user interface, the availability, and the file formats used for each algorithm (Table 2). The main advanced features were the ability to identify chemically equivalent atoms and reaction centres, and the option to map hydrogen atoms (Table 3). We also compared additional features, such as the ability to map all atoms in each reaction, the ability to map R groups and the consideration of reactant stereochemistry. Advanced features can be particularly important for certain applications of atom mapping [24–26].Table 2
Comparison of technical features
ApproachInterfaceAvailabilityInput file formatsOutput file formats
RDTStructure-basedWeb and desktop applicationFreeRXN, SMILESRXN, SMILES
DREAMOptimisation-basedWeb applicationFreeRXN, SMILESRXN
MWEDOptimisation-basedDesktop applicationFree for academicsRXN, SMILESSMILES, MetaCyc
CLCAStructure-basedAlgorithmFreeSMILESSMILES
